Companies keep announcing “futuristic” offices like they’ve reinvented the laws of physics… then reveal a cubicle with a chair, a desk, and a ficus. In this video, we tour the most aggressively normal “innovation campuses,” “collaboration zones,” and “future of work” sardine cans corporate America has ever posted on LinkedIn.

Hidden ovals, tire-tread ceilings, collab zones, design labs that look identical to collab zones—every company claims they’re building the future while forcing employees to commute just to sit in an open room they could’ve avoided by staying at home.

From AI firms bragging about storage closets to Fortune 500s flexing their cafeteria lighting, we’re breaking down why every “innovative workspace” looks exactly the same… and why companies keep pretending this is the future of work.

How “futuristic” is your office? Let me know in the comments.
